THE SEQUEL IS BETTER MONTH AT THE PARKWAY!

Thursday, January 18, 2024

7 pm Doors // 7:30 pm Trivia // 8 pm Movie

$9 Advance // $12 Door

Ticket purchases are final and non-refundable

Facebook RSVP

Directed by Francis Ford Coppola // Rated R

The compelling sequel to "The Godfather," contrasting the life of Corleone father and son. The trials of Michael Corleone (Al Pacino) are traced to 1958 and that of a young immigrant Vito Corleone (Robert De Niro) introduced to a life of crime in 1917's Hell's Kitchen. The neighborhood, not the restaurant.
